x4freetext: Same values,in Spanish
Neutron activation resonance integrals of Se-74,Se-78,
RA-1
Central reflector and thermal column of react.RA1
Flux in the reflector position was 2x10e12 n/cm2xs and
in the thermal column 10e+11 n/cm2xs
Solution containing standard and unknown in the desired
proportions.Aliquots of 0.1 Ml were dried on small
pieces of filter paper and sealed into plastic bags.
Total diameter less than 1cm.
Pairs of samples containing the same proportions of
unknown element and standard,in order to give approxi-
mately equal unknown and standard gamma-ray intensities
in the gamma-ray spectrum,were irradiated bare and Cd
covered(cadmium ratio method) or in two neutron spectra
with widely different resonance neutron fractions (two
spectrum method).The gamma-ray spectra of the two
samples were then measured and the relative number of
counts in the photopeaks calculated.Both methods give
the relative ratio of resonance-to-thermal capture
for unknown and standard. Only ratios of ratios were
measured,except for measurement of the cadmium ratio to
gold,to obtain epithermal spectral index of the neutron
spectra. Measurements were made only on well-resolved
and well separated peaks.
Encapsulated Li-Ge diode with an effective volume
of 5 cm3 and a resolution of 2.5 keV FWHM  for the
Gd-153 gamma rays at 96.7 and 103.4 keV.
Parameter measured was S0,equal to 2/sqrt(pi) times the
ratio of the reduced resonance integral to the thermal
absorption cross section. The S0 values were obtained
through the cadmium ratios.
Unknown cross sections assumed to be 1/v below cadmium
cutoff. Transmission of cadmium for resonance neutrons
calculated with the infinite slab approximation,using
the absorption cross section as a transmission cross
section
All S0 values were determined relative to gold,with an
assumed value S0(Au)=17.7. For activities with shorter
half lives in-115 was used as a secondary standard with
a value S0(in-115)=18.7+-0.1,which was determined by
using gold as standard. Resonance-integral value
deduced from ratio of resonance-to-thermal capture
by multiplying by the thermal absorption cross section
taken from Hughes and Schwarz (BNL-325,2Nd ed. 1958)
G.Ricabarra, 22 March 1973
BIB section updated
Corrections were made for the continuum and counter
background,for resonance self-shielding and for neutron
spectrum deviation from the 1/E form.
Error quoted is standard error of average value of the
ratio of ratios obtained from several irradiations.

x4freetext: Ratio of the reduced resonance integral to the
absorption cross section
Measurements made relative to the 412keV gold gamma-ray
by measuring the 265-keV,280-keV and 405-keV gamma-rays
of Se-75. The three cadmium ratios agreed to within
0.5%. Self-shielding was negligible. Applied a
-3% spectrum correction.
at energy E0= 0.025 eV
Measured S0 value  S0=10.3+-0.1

x4freetext: Reduced resonance integral and ratio to thermal sigma
Measurement of the 103-keV gamma ray from Se-81(62 min)
relative to the 136-keV gamma ray from Se-75 gave value
of S0 for formation of the isomeric state. Used yields
of Bishop et al.(NP 60 241 1964) to obtain total S0.
Applied a - 13% spectrum correction
for value of S0 for isomeric state see 30129.020
at energy E0= 0.025 eV
Measured S0 value, S0=2.65+-0.02

x4freetext: Reduced resonance integral and ratio to thermal sigma
The 554- and 620-keV gamma rays of Br-82 were measured
relative to the 412-keV gold gamma ray, samples with
1.0,2.0 and 20.4 millig/cm2 of Br-81 with bromine-gold
ratio of 156 to 1 were used.Transmission of cadmium for
resonance neutrons deduced of 20.4 millig/cm2 sample
measurements.Cadmium ratio measurements used to
evaluate self shielding. Final result includes a -9%
spectrum correction.
at energy E0= 0.025 eV
Only 2.2% of the desintegrations by-pass the ground
state,so this S0 value should be very closed to
that for total capture.
Measured S0 value was S0=24.3+-0.4

x4freetext: Reduced resonance integral and ratio to thermal sigma
The 150-keV gamma-ray of Te-131 was measured relative
to the 137-keV gamma ray of 54 min In-116.
Self-shielding in both tellurium and indium negligible.
no spectrum correction.
Isomeric yield is the same for resonance and thermal
neutron capture,so that value obtained also applies for
the total capture cross section
at energy E0= 0.025 eV
Measured S0 value was S0=2.10+-0.07

x4freetext: Reduced resonance integral and ratio to thermal sigma
Cadmium ratio for capture in Ba-138 leading to 85-min
Ba-139 was measured relative to 54-min in-116. Relative
intensities of the 166-keV gamma-ray of Ba-139 and the
137-keV gamma ray of in-116 were measured over two
Ba-139 half lives.
No neutron spectrum correction was applied
at energy E0= 0.025 eV
Measured S0 value was S0= 0.649+-0.004
